cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) and Face Expression Recognition (FER) using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses emotional intelligence and related disciplines, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper proposes data augmentation techniques and discusses the high number of parameters to learn, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework and discusses the achieved results, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
